If that's what you think it's going to trade to, put your limit order to cover your shorts

21:09.800 --> 21:15.920
if you're short at 1.0905.

21:15.920 --> 21:20.000
You're not going to get the best exit that way, but you have a spread that you have to

21:20.000 --> 21:24.040
incorporate when you're working with 4X and FX pairs.

21:24.120 --> 21:29.280
And I've had a lot of this happen over the years as an FX trader where my limit order

21:29.280 --> 21:33.600
was a little too overzealous.

21:33.600 --> 21:36.200
I was trying to be a little too perfect.

21:36.200 --> 21:46.820
And I've had many amazing exits elude me because of my overzealous targeting.

21:46.820 --> 21:51.200
So be a little bit more forgiving when you're trading, especially 4X, you've got to incorporate

21:51.200 --> 21:52.200
the spread.

21:52.200 --> 21:55.040
And I know some of you have brokers where it's like, oh, I have a really tight spread.

21:55.040 --> 21:56.040
Let me tell you something.

21:56.040 --> 21:58.760
Every broker has the ability to open that spread up on you.

21:58.760 --> 22:02.720
You're seeing the best case scenario when that ticker is showing.

22:02.720 --> 22:09.720
But trust me, when it's advantageous for them, they'll work it in their behalf, not yours.

22:09.720 --> 22:11.720
So make it easier for yourself.

22:11.720 --> 22:14.520
Just fluff up your exits with five pips.

22:14.520 --> 22:17.720
And if you're really new, just use 10 pips.

22:17.720 --> 22:20.760
And if you're struggling with the idea that, oh, I don't want to do that, I'll give up

22:21.760 --> 22:26.160
Well, let me show you this.

22:26.160 --> 22:29.920
This would be your entry candle, trading right back to this old high here.

22:29.920 --> 22:33.840
So one pip at or thereabouts.

22:33.840 --> 22:40.640
Once it hits that candle with this run here, that right there would be your entry candle.

22:40.640 --> 22:43.360
Your stop would be right above this candle's high.

22:43.360 --> 22:47.760
Now if you're scared or whatever, you can use this swing high and that's fine.

22:47.760 --> 22:57.560
Now in terms of math, the entry price would be 1.09653 and your stop would be 1.09728

22:57.560 --> 22:58.880
hypothetically.

22:58.880 --> 23:01.040
That's not a lot of pips.

23:01.040 --> 23:03.520
I would generally round that to 10.

23:03.520 --> 23:08.440
Even though it's not technically 10 pips here, I would round it to 10 and just be done with

23:08.440 --> 23:09.640
it.

23:09.640 --> 23:17.000
And looking at that model here, and you're aiming for that essentially 1.09 big figure,

23:17.000 --> 23:21.280
bluffing it up a little bit so our exit price would be a little bit higher than that.

23:21.280 --> 23:25.160
You guys see these things all the time and I just felt like using it, you know, just

23:25.160 --> 23:28.240
because I want to be cool.

