So it's a matter of adjusting to what it is you're trying to trade and then there's a

24:13.720 --> 24:18.400
little bit of rule following that you have to know when it comes to index trading and

24:18.400 --> 24:19.400
FX.

24:19.400 --> 24:23.640
FX predominantly, you're working with 7 o'clock in the morning to 10 o'clock in the morning.

24:23.640 --> 24:28.120
That's your New York open kill zone.

24:28.120 --> 24:38.360
Index trading, I'm focusing on 830 to 11 and I can take a trade all the way up to 1040-1045

24:38.360 --> 24:39.640
and still be okay.

24:39.720 --> 24:47.080
I'm not interested in taking new trades generally after 10 o'clock in the morning in the FX pair

24:48.040 --> 24:56.360
unless there is a news driver like we had this morning with the ISM number, the PMI number I

24:56.360 --> 24:57.400
mentioned earlier in the video.

24:58.520 --> 25:04.440
